definition.value: A chemical descriptor is a data item (quantity or value) about a chemical entity that conforms to a specification for how it is calculated, measured or recorded.
A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's  dimension of extension to the circumference of a circle or sphere.
Atomic radius is the 1D extent of the electron cloud surrounding the atom.
Bond multiplicity is the extent to which participating electrons are localized in the bonding orbitals.

A bond multiplicity descriptor is a chemical descriptor that in primitive cases is defined as half of the difference between the number of bonding and antibonding electrons in a particular system, but may also be defined with relation to the strength of a single bond.
A charge descriptor is a chemical descriptor which indicates the charge of a chemical entity.
A bond length descriptor is a dimensional extent descriptor which gives the measured or predicted (idealised) length of an atom to atom bond within a chemical entity.

The quality of an atom in which the 2s orbital mixes with only one of the three p-orbitals resulting in two sp orbitals and two remaining unchanged p orbitals. spsp overlap between two atoms form a s bond and two additional p bonds formed by pp overlap.
Half the sum of all the distance matrix entries with a value of 3
software execution is a process in which the instruction set that comprises the software program is executed on a machine.

definition.value: a generic SMILES descriptor is a SMILES descriptor that denotes only the labeled molecular graph (i.e. atoms and bonds, but no chiral or isotopic information).
